<STRONG>RECLAIMING A HERITAGE:</STRONG><BR>
<EM>Members of the Ohana Council erected an ancient Hawaiian shrine on Makapuu Beach.  Known as the most radical of Hawaii's sovereignty groups, they also distributed leaflets encouraging non-Hawaiian tourists to leave the islands.</EM>
