<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Nation of Hawaii challenges First Hawaiian Bank</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="flagsm.gif" BORDER="0"></A> Return to the <A HREF="index.html">Nation of Hawai`i Home Page</A><BR><IMG SRC="hrcolor2.gif"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.fhb.com/"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="fhb.gif" BORDER="1" HSPACE="4" VSPACE="4"></A><H1>Nation of Hawaii challenges First Hawaiian Bank</H1></CENTER>The Nation of Hawai`i is currently challenging First Hawaiian Bank on a number of fronts, concerning systematic discrimination against Native Hawaiian communities and violation of federal anti-trust laws. Protests have been filed with the Federal Reserve Bank in San Francisco and the Department of Justice, under <A HREF="constitution.html#art17">Article XVII (Transitional Provisions)</A> of the <A HREF="constitution.html">Hawaii Constitution</A>.<P><UL><A HREF="fh-fed.html">COMMENTS  BEFORE THE FEDERAL RESERVE BANK OF SAN FRANCISCO ON THE APPLICATION OF FIRST HAWAIIAN BANK TO ACQUIRE PACIFIC ONE BANK AND IDAHO FIRST BANK, January 17, 1996</A><P><A HREF="fh-doj.html">Letter to the Department of Justice regarding:<BR>Proposed Order Modifying Consent Final Judgement<BR>Civil No. 90-00904 DAE<BR>US v. First Hawaiian &amp; First Interstate, February 18, 1996</A></UL><P><A HREF="fh-press1.html">Press Release: Maui Demonstration - "Thumbs Down" to First Hawaiian, February 27, 1996</A><P><IMG SRC="hrcolor2.gif"><BR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="flagsm.gif" BORDER="0"></A> Return to the <A HREF="index.html">Nation of Hawai`i Home Page</A><BR></BODY></HTML>
