</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Kanahele conviction thrown out</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="flagsm.gif" BORDER="0" HSPACE="4" VSPACE="4"></A> Return to the <A HREF="index.html">Hawaiian Independence Home Page</A>, or the <A HREF="news.html">News Articles Index</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="hrcolor2.gif"><BR>
<CENTER><H1>Kanahele conviction thrown out</H1>

<B>Garden Island News<BR>
August 29, 1996, Thursday </B></CENTER>
<P>
Honolulu (AP) -- Hawaiian soverignty leader Dennis "Bumpy" Kanahele has won a legal round in state court.
<P>
Last October, Honolulu District Judge James Dannenburg found Kanahele guilty of driving without a valid driver's license.
<P>
On Wednesday, the state Supreme Court overturned the misdemeanor conviction.
<P>
Kanehele had originally been charged with driving with a suspended or revoked license.
<P>
The basis of the appeal was that the original charge was orally amended the day of the trial.
<P>
Even the state admitted the conviction couldn't stand because of the error.
<P>

