<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Data Reporting Manual
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<BODY   BACKGROUND="../logo/gaw.gif"   TEXT="#000000"   LINK="#0000FF"  VLINK="#FF0000"   ALINK="#00FFFF">

<H1><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<B>Data Reporting Manual of the WMO WDCGG</B></P></H1>
<H2><P ALIGN=CENTER>
Volume IV-Greenhouse Gases and Other Atmospheric Gases
<BR><BR>
WDCGG No. 1</P></H2>
<HR SIZE=5>
<B>
<FONT SIZE=+2>T</FONT>he WMO Executive Council at its forty-second session (Geneva, June 1990) requested
that the Secretary-General urge Members to submit relevant past and current data to the
WDCGG to enable it to play its unique role as the complete depository of data on greenhouse
and other atmospheric gases.
</B>
<HR SIZE=5>

<BR><BR>

<B><H1><P ALIGN=CENTER>
Contents</P></H1>

<DIR>
<LI><A HREF="Introduction.html">Introduction</A>

<LI><A HREF="FDDRProcedure.html">Floppy Disk Data Reporting Procedures</A>

<LI><A HREF="CSDRProcedure.html">Coding Sheet Data Reporting Procedures</A>

<LI><IMG SRC="../logo/New.gif"><A HREF="ViaInternet.html">Via Internet Data Reporting Procedure</A>

<LI><A HREF="SRProcedure.html">Station Report Procedures</A>

<LI><A HREF="FigureAndTable.html">Figures and Tables</A>

<LI>Appendix: <A HREF="EditorUtilization.html">Editor Utilization</A>
</DIR>

<HR>
<PRE>
Please send the observation data with cover letter to the following address:

   WMO World Data Centre for Greenhouse Gases (WDCGG)
   Japan Meteorological Agency
   1-3-4 Otemachi, chiyoda-ku
   TOKYO, 100
   Japan

In addition, send a copy of cover letter describing the content of the data to:

   Environment Division
   World Meteorological Organization
   P.O. Box No.2300
   CH-1211 GENEVA 2
   Switzerland
</PRE>
<HR>

<FONT SIZE=+1>F</FONT>or further information contact:
<p>
Dr. Takayo MATSUO, Head<BR>
WMO WDCGG<BR>
Japan Meteorological Agency<BR>
1-3-4 Otemachi, Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo 100<BR>
Japan<BR><BR>
Facsimile: +81-3-3211-4640<BR>
e-mail :  <A  HREF="mailto:wdcgg@hq.kishou.go.jp">wdcgg@hq.kishou.go.jp</A>
</B>
