<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Amsterdam Island Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/Amsterdam-FLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Amsterdam Island Station, France
</H1>
</CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1981 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Amsterdam Island       <B>Country/Trretory</B> : France                   <B>Submmited by</B> : Centre des Faibles Radioactivites (CFR)
<B>Latitude</B>  : 37&#176; 48&#180; S              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 77&#176; 32&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 65  m                  <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="AmsterdamIslandCFR-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> P. Monfray, V. Kazan, G. Bonsang, A. Gaudry and G. Lambert

<B>Organization :</B> CFR (Centre des Faibles Radioactivites)
               Laboratoire mixte CNRS (Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique)/CEA (Commisariat l'nergie Atomique)
               Avenue de la Terrasse,
               91 198 Gif-sur-Yvette Cedex,
               France

<B>Location     :</B> 1981-1985   37&#176; 48&#180; S, 77&#176; 32&#180; E,
               1986-1987   37&#176; 41&#180; S, 77&#176; 47&#180; E,
               1988-       37&#176; 48&#180; S, 77&#176; 32&#180; E, 65 m above mean sea level

<B>Topography around the station :</B> Coastal area

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
   1981-1984   Continuous NDIR analyzer URAS-2T.
   1985        Continuous NDIR analyzer URAS-2T. The air is dried at a temperature between -70&#176;C and -35&#176;C with a further correction
               of the eventual influence of the moisture.
   1986-1990   Continuous NDIR analyzer URAS-2T. The air is dried at a temperature between -70&#176;C and -55&#176;C with a further correction
               of the eventual influence of the moisture.
   1991-       Continuous NDIR analyzer Siemens Ultrmat 5F.

<B>Sampling interval :</B> 10 seconds.

<B>Calibration interval :</B>
   1 hour. Data with hourly standard deviation greater than 0.5 ppmv are rejected.

<B>Calibration gases :</B>
   1981-1982   CO<SUB>2</SUB> in N<SUB>2</SUB> certified by WMO CCL (Central CO<SUB>2</SUB> Laboratory in SIO, University of California, San Diego, USA).
   1983-1985   Field standards of CO<SUB>2</SUB> in N<SUB>2</SUB> were used. The carrier gas effect has been determined by means of two scales, the first one in N<SUB>2</SUB>,
               the second one in air, both of them certified by the WMO CCL.
   1986-       Field standards of CO<SUB>2</SUB> in air were used.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   1981-1989   WMO X85 scale.
   1990-       CFR90 scale, intercompared in 1990 with the SIO scale in use at Baring Head, New Zealand, within 0.1 ppmv.

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   Prevailing wind directions are SW to NW.

   1981-1982   Data representative for marine sector (270&#176; through 040o clockwise) are selected.
   1983-1984   Data selected for winds superior to 4 m/s and marine sector (300&#176; through 040&#176; clockwise).
   1985-1989   Data are selected for winds from;
               (1) a sector of 300&#176; through 040&#176; clockwise with velocities higher than 4 m/s,
               (2) a sector of 260&#176; through 300&#176; clockwise with velocities higher than 8 m/s,
   1990-       Data are selected for winds from;
               (1) a sector of 300&#176; through 050&#176; clockwise with velocities higher than or equal to 5 m/s,
               (2) a sector of 260&#176; through 300&#176; clockwise with velocities higher than 8 m/s,
   Note: The lack of the data from January 1985 to March 1985 is due to the interruption of the measurements during
         the building of the new station.

<B>Literature references to programme :</B>
   Gaudry A., J.M. Ascencio-Parvy, and G. Lambert, 1983: Preliminary Study of CO<SUB>2</SUB> Variation at Amsterdam Island (Territoire des Terres
         Australes et Antarctiques Franaises). <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 88, 1323-1329.
   Ascencio-Parvy J.M., A. Gaudry and G. Lambert, 1984: Year-to-year CO2 variations at Amsterdam Island in 1980-1983. <I>Geoph. Res. Lett.</I>,
         11, 1215-1217.
   Gaudry A., P. Monfray, G. Polian and G. Lambert, 1987: The 1982-1983 El-Ni&ntilde;o: a 6 Billion Ton CO2 release. <I>Tellus</I>, 39B, 209-213. 
   Monfray P., A. Gaudry, G. Polian and G. Lambert, 1987: Seasonal variations of atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> in the Southern Indian Ocean. <I>Tellus</I>, 39B, 67-71.
   Gaudry A., P. Monfray, G. Polian, G. Bonsang, B. Ardouin, A. Jegou, and G. Lambert, 1990: Non-seasonal variations of atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB>
         concentrations at Amsterdam Island. <I>Tellus</I>, 43B, 136-143.




</PRE>
