<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Cape Matatula Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/CapeMatatulaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Cape Matatula Station, USA<BR>
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1976 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Cape Matatula, Samoa <B>Country/Trretory</B> : USA                      <B>Submmited by</B> : NOAA/CMDL
<B>Latitude</B>  :  14&#176; 15&#180; S           <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 170&#176; 34&#180; W           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 30 m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="CapeMatatulaCMDL-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Pieter Tans, Kirk Thoning and Lee Waterman

<B>Organization :</B> NOAA/Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory 
               (CMDL, former Geophysical Monitoring for Climatic Change)

<B>Address      :</B> 325 Broadway, Boulder, Colorado 80303, USA

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
               14&#176; 15&#180; S, 170&#176; 34&#180; W, 30 m, tropical Pacific island

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B> NDIR continuous

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B> Monitor atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> increase

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   Within hour variability, hour to hour differences

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   1976-1981   CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-N<SUB>2</SUB>
   1981-       CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   X1985 Scripps mole fraction

<B>Literature references to programme :</B>
   GMCC, 1981: Annual Report No. 10. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B. Bodhaine and J. Harris, eds.).
   GMCC, 1982: Annual Report No. 11. U.S. Department of Commerce, NOAA (J. Harris and B. Bodhaine, eds.).
   GMCC, 1983: Summary Report No. 12. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Harris and E. Nickerson, eds.).
   GMCC, 1984: Annual Report No. 13. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (E. Nickerson, ed.).
   GMCC, 1985: Annual Report No. 14. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (R. Schnell, ed.).
   GMCC, 1987: Annual Report No. 16. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B. Bodhaine, ed.).
   Halter, B.C., J.M. Harris, and T.J. Conway, 1988: Component signals in the record of atmospheric carbon dioxide
      concentration at American Samoa. <I>J. Geophy. Res.</I>, 93, 15914-15918.
   GMCC, 1988: Annual Report No. 17. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Elkins, ed.).
   Waterman, L.S., D.W. Nelson, W.D. Komhyr, T.B. Harris, K.W. Thoning, and P.P. Tans,1989: Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide
      Measurements at Cape Matatula, American Samoa, 1976-1987. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 94, 14817-14829.
   GMCC, 1989: Annual Report No. 18. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (W. Komhyr, ed.).


</PRE>
