<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of K-puszta Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/K-pusztaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
K-puszta Station, Hungary
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1984 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : K-puszta               <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Hungary                  <B>Submmited by</B> : Hungarian Meteorological Service, Institute for Atmospheric Physics
<B>Latitude</B>  : 46&#176; 58&#180; N              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 19&#176; 33&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X74 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 125  m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="K-puszta-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Author       :</B> L. Haszpra

<B>Organization :</B> Hungarian Meteorological Service, Institute for Atmospheric Physics

<B>Address      :</B> H-1675 Budapest, P.O.Box 39, Hungary

<B>Site position and description :</B>
   46&#176; 58&#180; N, 19&#176; 33&#180; E.  Elevation: 125 m.
   Clearing in a pine forest on the Hungarian Great Plain.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement technique :</B>
   Continuous sampling, monitoring with SIEMENS Ultramat-3 analyzer.  Data collection half-hourly.
   Air sample from an intake at 10 m above the ground.
   The instrument was broken down in 1987.

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>
   CO<SUB>2</SUB> monitoring in rural continental region involving monitoring the trend.

<B>Data selection procedures :</B>
   Only technically false data are eliminated.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   CO<SUB>2</SUB> in N<SUB>2</SUB> calibration gases with 304.67 and 383.92 ppm.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   WMO-1974 Mole Fraction Scale.



</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
