<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Kollumerwaard Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/KollumerwaardLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Kollumerwaard Station, Netherlands
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : July 1991 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Kollumerwaard       <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Netherlands              <B>Submmited by</B> : Air Research Laboratory
<B>Latitude</B>  : 53&#176; 20&#180; N           <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : GC-FID
<B>Longitude</B> : 06&#176; 17&#180; E           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : USA Standard Gas (NIST)
<B>Altitude</B>  : 0 m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Kollumerwaard-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> J.P. Beck     

<B>Organization :</B> Air Research Laboratory, The Netherlands

<B>Address      :</B> National Institute of Public Health and Environmental Protection
               P.O. Box 1, 3720 BA Bilthoven
               The Netherlands 

<B>Location     :</B> 53&#176; 20&#180; 02" N, 06&#176; 16&#180; 38" E, elevation 0 meter above mean sea level,

<B>Topography around the station :</B>
   The station is located in an agricultural area.   The nearest town is the city of Groningen
   (168,000 inhabitants) at a distance of about 25 km in ESE direction.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement technique :</B>
   A Chromo-pack GC (type CP 9000) is operated with three columns in series, packed with
   HayeSep (1 and 2) and Molecular sieve (3) respectively.   Following sample injection,
   backflush and heart-cut techniques are performed using two 10 port switching valves.   After
   separation, components are led to a hydrogen-fed Ni catalyst (methanizer) where CO<SUB>2</SUB> and CO
   are converted to CH<SUB>4</SUB>.   Final detection is done by means of a flame ionization detector (FID).
   From the 2 inch sample stack air is led through 1/4 inch Stainless Steel tubing at s flow rate
   of 5 litres/minute using a critical orifice and a vacuum pump to a dual Perma Pure Dryer
   system (PermaPure type MD-125-12S).

<B>Sampling Interval :</B> 15 minutes

<B>Calibration :</B>
   Performed every month using computer-controlled massflow dilution of a standard gas
   mixture (CO, CH<SUB>4</SUB>, CO<SUB>2</SUB> and C<SUB>3</SUB>H<SUB>8</SUB> ; C<SUB>3</SUB>H<SUB>8</SUB> representing NMHC) at 6 individual levels for
   each component in its relevant concentration range.

<B>Calibration gases :</B> NIST reference materials


</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
<CENTER>
| <A HREF="/wdcgg.html">Home</A> |<BR>
