<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Kosan Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/KosanLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Kosan Station, Korea, Rep. of
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : August 1990 - June 1994
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Kosan                   <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Korea, Rep. of           <B>Submmited by</B> : Meteorological Research Institute/KMA
<B>Latitude</B>  :  33&#176; 17&#180; N              <B>Time Interval</B>    : By Event                 <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 126&#176; 09&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 72  m                   <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Kosan-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> CHO, HA-MAN, KIM, KYUNG-RYUL and NAM, JAE-CHOL

<B>Organization :</B> Meteorological Research Institute, Korea Meteorological Administration

<B>Address      :</B> 2, Waryong-Dong, Chongno-Gu, Seoul, Korea

<B>Site position and description :</B>
   33&#176; 17&#180; N, 126&#176; 09&#180; E, 72 m msl, Island sea shore

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement techniques :</B>
   Vacuum Pyrex grass flask(3l), once a week and NDIR

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air working calibration gases used.  These were calibrated at Scripps Institute of Oceanograph.  The concentration of WMO secondary standard
   gases were covered the range 345-372 ppmv.

<B>Data selection procedures :</B> simultaneous sampled air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> X1985 WMO mole fraction scale

<B>Scientific aim and scope :</B>
   Monitoring the background concentration of atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> and trends analysis.

<B>Literature references to the programme :</B>
   CDIAC 1990 ; Trends '90 A compendium of Data on Global Change.  The Carbon Dioxide Information Analysis Center, Oak Ridge National Laboratory, USA.




</PRE>
