<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Lampedusa Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/LampedusaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Lampedusa, Italy
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : May 1992 - September 1994
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Lampedusa, Sicily   <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Italy                    <B>Submmited by</B> : ENEA CRE Casaccia
<B>Latitude</B>  : 35&#176; 31&#180; N           <B>Time Interval</B>    : By Event                 <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 12&#176; 38&#180; E           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : SIO93 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 85 m                <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Lampedusa-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> L. Ciattaglia,  P. Chamard

<B>Organization :</B> ENEA, Italy

<B>Address      :</B> ENEA Amb/Clim Casaccia, P.O. Box 2400, 00100 Rome, Italy

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   35&#176; 31&#180; 00&quot; N, 12&#176; 37&#180; 30&quot; E, elevation 85 m.
   Island, sea shore (rocky), South of Sicily, in the middle of the Mediterranean Sea.  Prevailing
   winds are N/NW and S.  Climate is temperate and dry, precipitation maximum is in the winter.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
        Air samples are taken every friday with two pairs of glass flasks through a chemical water vapor
   trap, and pressurized at 280-300 kPa. 
        CO<SUB>2</SUB> concentration is determined at the Laboratory in Rome (ENEA). 
        Instrument type is NDIR analyzer Ultramat 5E Siemens.  Water vapour is removed by cold trap
   (-65 &#176;C) in the measuring phase.

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   The only selection applied refers to the consistency of values of pairs.
   If different more than 0.5 ppm, the values are rejected.  The reported values are the arithmetic mean.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> CO<SUB>2</SUB> in synthetic air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> SIO 93 Scale


</PRE>
<B>
