<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Langenbrugge Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/LangenbruggeLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Langenbr&uuml;gge Station, Germany
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1972 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Langenbr&uuml;gge           <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Germany                  <B>Submmited by</B> : Umweltbundesamt
<B>Latitude</B>  : 52&#176; 48&#180; N              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 10&#176; 46&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : 1987 Mole Fraction Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 74  m                  <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Langenbrugge-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> W. Fricke

<B>Organization :</B> Umweltbundesamt, Germany

<B>Address      :</B> Frankfurter Str. 135, D-6050 Offenbach/Main, Federal republic of Germany

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   52&#176; 48&#180; N; 10&#176; 46&#180; E, 74 m.
   North German lowland, agricultural and forest environment, some influences from pollution sources.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
   Continuous monitoring with Siemens ULTRAMAT-3, with water vapour controlled.
   Daily values are calculated on the basis of half-hourly mean values.

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   Only technically biased values are removed (caused by calibration or malfunction of equipment).

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> CO<SUB>2</SUB> in N<SUB>2</SUB>

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   Carrier gas corrections have been determined experimentally and applied based on five CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air standards calibrated by
   Scripps Institution of Oceanography in 1988.
   Rel. precision of half-hourly readings: about 1 ppmv.




</PRE>
<B>
