<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Mace Head Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/MaceHead-CFRLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Mace Head Station, Ireland
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : July 1992 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Mace Head           <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Ireland                  <B>Submmited by</B> : Centre des Faibles Radioactivites (CFR)
<B>Latitude</B>  : 53&#176; 19&#180; N           <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 09&#176; 53&#180; W           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : CFR90 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 11 m                <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="MaceHeadCFR-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> A. Gaudry, V. Kazan, P. Monfray <SUP>(*1)</SUP>
               T. O'Connor, G. Jennings <SUP>(*2)</SUP>
               P. Simmonds <SUP>(*3)</SUP>

<B>Organization :</B> CFR (Centre des Faibles Radioactivites), University College of Galway, International Science Consultants

<B>Address      :</B> <SUP>(*1)</SUP> CFR (Centre des Faibles Radioactivites)
                    Laboratoire de Modelisation du Climat et de l'Environnement / Centre d'Etude de Saclay
                    batiment 709, Orme des Merisiers,
                    91 191 Gif-sur-Yvette Cedex,
                    France

               <SUP>(*2)</SUP> University College of Galway, Department of Physics,
                    Galway, Ireland

               <SUP>(*3)</SUP> International Science Consultants,
                    39, Avon Castle Drive, Ringwood Hants, BH24 2BB,
                    United Kingdom

<B>Site position and description :</B>
   Latitude 53&#176; 19&#180; N, longitude 09&#176; 53&#180; W,  elevation 11 m above mean sea level. Coastal area.
   Prevailing wind directions are SW to NW.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement techniques :</B>
   Continuous NDIR analyzer Siemens Ultramat 5F.
   Sampling interval is 10s.  Calibration interval is 2 hours.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> field standards of CO<SUB>2</SUB> in air

<B>Data selection procedures :</B>
   Data are selected for winds from a sector of 200&#176; to 300&#176; clockwise with velocities
   higher than 4 m/s.
   We take into account only mean CO<SUB>2</SUB> concentrations corresponding to at least 4
   consecutive hours of background conditions.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   CFR90 scale, prepared by means of an accurate gravimetric method, and then intercompared in 1990 with the SIO scale
   in use at Baring Head, New Zealand, within 0.1ppmv.


</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
<CENTER>
