<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Mauna Loa (in situ) Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/MaunaLoaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Mauna Loa Station, USA
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : May 1974 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Mauna Loa, Hawaii   <B>Country/Trretory</B> : USA                      <B>Submmited by</B> : NOAA/CMDL
<B>Latitude</B>  :  19&#176; 32&#180; N          <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 155&#176; 35&#180; W          <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 3397 m              <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="MaunaLoaCMDL-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Pieter Tans, Kirk Thoning and Lee Waterman

<B>Organization :</B> NOAA/Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory (CMDL) 
               (former Geophysical Monitoring for Climatic Change)

<B>Address      :</B> 325 Broadway,  Boulder,  Colorado 80303, U.S.A.

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
               19&#176; 32&#180; N, 155&#176; 35&#180; W, 3397 m,
               volcanic island, tropical Pacific

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
               NDIR continuous

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>
               Monitor atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> increase

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
               Within hour variability,  hour to hour variability.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
               1973-1981    CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-N<SUB>2</SUB>
               1981-        CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
               X1985 Scripps mole fraction scale

<B>Literature references to programme :</B>
   GMCC, 1981: Annual Report No.10. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B.Bodhaine, J. Harris, eds.).
   GMCC, 1982: Annual Report No.11. U.S. Department of Commerce, NOAA (J. Harris and B. Bodhaine, eds.).
   GMCC, 1983: Summary Report No.12. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Harris and E. Nickerson, eds.).
   GMCC, 1984: Annual Report No.13. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (E. Nickerson,ed.).
   GMCC, 1985: Annual Report No.14. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (R. Schnell, ed.).
   GMCC, 1987: Annual Report No.16. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B. Bodhaine, ed.).
   GMCC, 1988: Annual Report No.17. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Elkins, ed.).
   GMCC, 1989: Annual Report No.18. NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (W. Komhyr, ed.).
   Komhyr, W.D., T.B. Harris, L.S. Waterman, J.F.S. Chin, and K.W. Thoning, 1989: Atmospheric carbon dioxide
      at Mauna Loa Observatory: 1. NOAA/GMCC measurements with a nondispersive infrared analyzer, 1974-1985.
      <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 94, 8533- 8547.
   Thoning, K.W., P.P. Tans, and W.D. Komhyr, 1989: Atmospheric carbon dioxide at Mauna Loa Observatory:
      2. Analysis of the NOAA/GMCC data, 1974-1985. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 94, 8549-8586.
   Peterson, J.T., W.D. Komhyr, L.S. Waterman, R.H. Gammon, K.W. Thoning, and T.J. Conway, 1986: Atmospheric
      CO<SUB>2</SUB> variations at Barrow, Alaska, 1973-1982. <I>J. Atmos. Chem.</I>, 4, 491-510.
   Gillette, D.A., W.D. Komhyr, L.S. Waterman, L.P. Steele, and R.H. Gammon, 1987: The NOAA/GMCC continuous
      CO<SUB>2</SUB> record at the South Pole, 1975-1982. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 92, 4231-4240.
   Thoning, K.W., 1989: Selection of NOAA/GMCC CO<SUB>2</SUB> data from Mauna Loa Observatory, In The Statistical Treatment
      of CO<SUB>2</SUB> Data Records.  NOAA Tech. Mem. (ERL-ARL-173), <I>Environ. Res. Lab.</I>, 131 pp.
   Waterman, L.S., D. W. Nelson, W.D. Komhyr, T.B. Harris, and K.W. Thoning, 1989: Atmospheric carbon dioxide
      measurements at Cape Matatula, American Samoa, 1976-1984. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 94, 14817-14829.


</PRE>
