<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Minamitorishima Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/MinamitorishimaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Minamitorishima Station, Japan
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : March 1993 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Minamitorishima     <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Japan                    <B>Submmited by</B> : Japan Meteorological Agency
<B>Latitude</B>  :  24&#176; 18&#180; N          <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 153&#176; 58&#180; E          <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 8 m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Minamitorishima-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Y.JOO, H.MIYAMOTO, T.KAGAWA, Y. HAYASHI, H.NAGAI, K. ISHII

<B>Organization :</B> Japan Meteorological Agency

<B>Address      :</B> Observations Division, Observations Department,
               Japan Meteorological Agency
               1-3-4 Otemachi, Chiyoda-ku, TOKYO 100, Japan

<B>Site position and description :</B>
   24&#176; 15&#180; N, 153&#176; 58&#180; E,  elevation 8 meter above mean sea level.
   Little isolated island, located in the western North Pacific Ocean.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement techniques :</B>
   Continuous NDIR analyzer, HORIBA VIA-510R.  The height of the intake is 20 meter above
   the ground.  The air is dried with a electronic cooler unit, perma-pure dryer, and a chemical dryer
   (Mg(ClO<SUB>4</SUB>)<SUB>2</SUB>) at a dew-point temperature about 5&#176;C, -30&#176;C, and -70&#176;C, respectively.  The
   calibration is carried out 2-hourly using quadratic calibration equation with 4 working standards.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> CO<SUB>2</SUB> in natural air

<B>Data selection procedures :</B>
   Daily data are selected under the condition with standard deviation of hourly mean data. For
   accumulated hourly data for one year, data selection procedure is applied by fitting the two
   harmonic and liner function curve with the least squares method.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> X1985 WMO mole fraction scale

<B>Scientific aim and scope :</B>
   To submit the critical data for research and study to reveal the long term trend and carbon cycle
   in the western North Pacific Ocean under the WMO GAW Network.


</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
