<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Monte Cimone Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/MonteCimoneLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Monte Cimone Station, Italy
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : March 1979 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Monte Cimone        <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Italy                    <B>Submmited by</B> : Italian Meteorological Service
<B>Latitude</B>  : 44&#176; 11&#180; N           <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 10&#176; 42&#180; E           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 2165 m              <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="MonteCimone-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> V. Cundari, T. Colombo, L. Ciattaglia

<B>Organization :</B> Italian Meteorological Service

<B>Address      :</B> 1) CAMM Mt.CIMONE, Via delle Ville 100, 41029-SESTOLA (MO),
                  ITALY (Dr.V.Cundari, Dr.T.Colombo)
               2) Vigna di Valle Observatory, 00062-BRACCIANO (ROMA),
                  ITALY (Dr.L. Tasso)

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   44&#176; 11&#180; N, 10&#176; 42&#180; E, Appenine mountain peak, no local sources of contamination, no
   access by road, altitude 2165 m msl, operational baseline station since June 1978.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
   1979-1987     Continuous sampling, NDIR URAS 2T analyzer
   1989-         Continuous NDIR analyzer ULTRAMAT-5E.
                 The air is dried at a temperature between -60&#176;C and -70&#176;C.

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>
   Studies of CO<SUB>2</SUB> sink and source in Mediterranean and European region;
   Study of long term trend of atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB>

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   1979-   Only technically invalid data are removed as long with those affected by verified local contamination.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   1981-1987     CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-N<SUB>2</SUB> by Scripps Institute of Oceanography
   1987-1991     Standards of CO<SUB>2</SUB> in Synthetic Air, measured by Scripps Institution of Oceanography
   1991-         Standard of CO<SUB>2</SUB> in Natural Air accorded to Scripps Scale.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   1979-         WMO X-85 scale in air

<B>Literature references to the programme :</B>
   Ciattaglia L., 1983: Interpretation of atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> measurements at Mt. Cimone (Italy) related to wind data.
      <I>J.G.R.</I>, 88, 1331-1338.
   Ciattaglia L. and T.Colombo, 1986: Atmospheric carbon dioxide measurements at Mt. Cimone, Italy (1979-1983).
      <I>Annales Geophysicae</I>, 4, b, 1, 13-20.
   Ciattaglia L., V. Cundari and T. Colombo, 1987: Further measurements of Atmospheric carbon dioxide at Mt. Cimone,
      Italy: 1979-1985. <I>Tellus</I>, 39B, 13-20.
   Cundari V., T. Colombo, G. Papini, G. Benedicti and L. Ciattaglia, 1990: Recent improvements on atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB>
      measurements at Mt.Cimone Observatory, Italy. <I>IL NUOVO CIMENTO</I>, 13 C, N.5, 871-882.


</PRE>
