<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Point Barrow Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/PointBarrowLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Point Barrow Station, USA
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : July 1973 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Point Barrow, Alaska <B>Country/Trretory</B> : USA                      <B>Submmited by</B> : NOAA/CMDL
<B>Latitude</B>  :  71&#176; 19&#180; N           <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 156&#176; 36&#180; W           <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 11 m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="PointBarrowCMDL-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Pieter Tans, Kirk Thoning and Lee Waterman

<B>Organization :</B> NOAA/Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory 
               (CMDL, former Geophysical Monitoring for Climatic Change)

<B>Address      :</B> 325 Broadway, Boulder, Colorado 80303, USA

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   71&#176; 19&#180; N, 156&#176; 36&#180; W,  11 m, Coast of Arctic Ocean

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B> NDIR continuous

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B> Monitor atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> increase

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   Within hour variability, hour to hour differences

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   1973-1981   CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-N<SUB>2</SUB>
   1981-       CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   X1985 Scripps mole fraction

<B>Literature references to programme :</B> 
   Peterson J.T., et al., 1982: <I>Tellus</I> 34, 166-175.
   GMCC, 1982: Annual Report No. 11.  U.S. Department of Commerce, NOAA (J. Harris and B. Bodhaine, eds.).
   GMCC, 1985: Annual Report No. 14.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (R. Schnell, ed.).
   GMCC, 1987: Annual Report No. 16.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B. Bodhaine, ed.).
   Peterson, J.T., W.D.Komhyr, L.S. Waterman, R.H. Gammon, K.W. Thoning, and T.J. Conway, 1986: Atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB>
      variations at Barrow, Alaska, 1973-1982. <I>J. Atmos. Chem.</I>, 4, 491-510.
   GMCC, 1988: Annual Report No. 17.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Elkins, ed.).
   GMCC, 1989: Annual Report No. 18.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (W. Komhyr, ed.).


</PRE>
