<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Ryori Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/RyoriLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Ryori Station, Japan
</H1>
</CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1987 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Ryori               <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Japan                    <B>Submmited by</B> : Japan Meteorological Agency
<B>Latitude</B>  :  39&#176; 02&#180; N          <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 141&#176; 50&#180; E          <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 230 m               <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Ryori-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Y. JOO, H. MIYAMOTO, T. KAGAWA, Y. HAYASHI, H. NAGAI, K. ISHII <SUP>1)</SUP>
               Y. DEGUCHI, K. HORIKAWA, S. MURAKAMI <SUP>2)</SUP>

<B>Organization :</B> Japan Meteorological Agency (JMA)

<B>Address      :</B> Data Management; 1) Observations Division, Observations Department,
                                   Japan Meteorological Agency,
                                   1-3-4 Otemachi, Chiyoda-ku, TOKYO 100, Japan

               Observation;     2) Meteorological Rocket Observation Station,
                                   Ryori, Sanriku-cho, Kesen-gun, IWATE 022-02, Japan

<B>Site position and description :</B>
   39&#176; 02&#180; N, 141&#176; 50&#180; E,  elevation 230 meter above mean sea level.
   Oceanic site facing the Pacific Ocean

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement techniques :</B>
   Continuous NDIR analyzer, HORIBA VIA-500R.  The height of the intake is 20 meter
   above the ground.  The air is dried with two electronic coolers and a freeze out dryer at a dew-point
   temperature about 5 &#176;C, -30 &#176;C, and -65 &#176;C, respectively.  The calibration is carried out 2-hourly
   using quadratic calibration equation with 4 working standards.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> CO<SUB>2</SUB> in natural air

<B>Data selection procedures :</B>
   Daily data are selected under the condition with standard deviation of hourly mean data.  For
   accumulated hourly data for one year, data selection procedure is applied by fitting the two
   harmonic and liner function curve with the least squares method.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> X1985 WMO mole fraction scale

<B>Scientific aim and scope :</B>
   To submit the critical data for research and study to reveal the long term trend and carbon
   cycle in the east coast of Asia under the WMO GAW Network.

<B>Literature references to the programme :</B>
   ITO T., M. SAITO, and T. KAGAWA, 1990: Carbon dioxide monitoring by Japan Meteorological Agency.
      Third International Conference on Analysis and Evaluation of Atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> Data Present and
      Past, WMO environmental report series, No.59, 262-267.


</PRE>
<B>
