<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Sable Island Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/SableIslandLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Sable Island Station, Canada
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : March 1975 - July 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Sable Island           <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Canada               <B>Submmited by</B> : Atmospheric Environment Service (AES)
<B>Latitude</B>  : 43&#176; 56&#180; N              <B>Time Interval</B>    : By Event                 <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 60&#176; 01&#180; W              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X83 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 5 m                    <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="SableIsland-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors :</B> N. Trivett (AES), V. Hudec (AES), and C. S. Wong (MCRC)

<B>Organization manning the BAPMoN sampling station :</B>
   Atmospheric Environment Service (AES), Department of the Environment,
   Air Quality and Inter-Environmental Research Branch

<B>Address :</B> 
   4905 Dufferin Street, Downsview, Ontario, Canada, M3H 5T4

<B>Organization manning the analytical and calibration laboratories :</B>
   (Prior to March 1989) Marine Carbon Research Centre (MCRC), Institute of Ocean Sciences,
   Oceans Sciences and Survey, Department of Fisheries and Oceans
   (March 1989 to present) Atmospheric Environment Service (AES), Department of the Environment,
   Air Quality and Inter-Environmental Research Branch

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   43&#176; 56&#180;N, 60&#176; 01&#180; W, elevation 5 m.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement technique :</B>
   Flask sampling, one flask pair per week, non-dispersive infrared analyzer.

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>
   Atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> time-series.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   (Prior to March 1989) CO<SUB>2</SUB>/N<SUB>2</SUB>, calibrated against Scripps reference gases.
   (March 1989 to present) CO<SUB>2</SUB>/Air, calibrated against Scripps reference gases.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   Converted from WMO-1974 (CO<SUB>2</SUB>/N<SUB>2</SUB>) scale to WMO-1983 (CO<SUB>2</SUB>/Air) scale.


</PRE>
<B>
