<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Schauinsland Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/SchauinslandLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Schauinsland Station, Germany
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : January 1972 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Schauinsland           <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Germany                  <B>Submmited by</B> : Umweltbundesamt
<B>Latitude</B>  : 47&#176; 55&#180; N              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> :  7&#176; 55&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X74 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 1205  m                <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Schauinsland-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> W. Fricke

<B>Organization :</B> Umweltbundesamt, Germany

<B>Address      :</B> Frankfurter Str. 135, D-6050 Offenbach/Main, Federal Republic of Germany

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   47&#176; 55&#180; N, 7&#176; 55&#180; E, elevation 1205 m.
   Black Forest mountain range, located on peak. Forest environment.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
   Continuous monitoring with Siemens ULTRAMAT-3 with water vapour controlled.
   Daily values are calculated on the basis of half-hourly mean values.

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   Only technically biased values are removed (caused by calibration or malfunction of equipment).

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   CO<SUB>2</SUB> in N<SUB>2</SUB>, from September 1, 1991: CO<SUB>2</SUB> in air.

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   Carrier gas corrections have been determined experimentally and applied until August 31, 1991 based on
   five CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air standards calibrated by Scripps Institution of Oceanography in 1988.
   Rel. precision of half-hourly readings: < 1 ppmv.




</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
<CENTER>
