<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of South Pole Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
South Pole Station, Antarctica<BR>
</P></H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : March 1975 - December 1992
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : South Pole, Antarctica <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Antarctica               <B>Submmited by</B> : NOAA/CMDL
<B>Latitude</B>  : 89&#176; 59&#180; S              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 24&#176; 48&#180; W              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 2810 m                 <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="SouthPoleCMDL-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Pieter Tans, Kirk Thoning and Lee Waterman

<B>Organization :</B> NOAA/Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory 
               (CMDL, former Geophysical Monitoring for Climatic Change)

<B>Address      :</B> 325 Broadway, Boulder, Colorado 80303, USA

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   89&#176; 59&#180; S, 24&#176; 48&#180; W, 2810 m, polar ice plateau

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B> NDIR continuous

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B> Monitor atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> increase

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B> Within hour variability, hour to hour differences

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> 1975-1980   CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-N<SUB>2</SUB>
                         1980-       CO<SUB>2</SUB>-in-air

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> X1985 Scripps mole fraction

<B>Literature references to programme :</B>
   DeLuisi, J., 1981: Geophysical Monitoring for Climatic Change Summary Report 1980.  U.S. Department of Commerce, NOAA, Environmental
      Research Laboratories.
   GMCC, 1982: Annual Report No. 11.  U.S. Department of Commerce, NOAA (J. Harris and B. Bodhaine, eds.).
   GMCC, 1983: Summary Report No. 12.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce, (J. Harris and E. Nickerson, eds.).
   GMCC, 1984: Annual Report No. 13.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (E. Nickerson, ed.).
   GMCC, 1985: Annual Report No. 14.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (R. Schnell, ed.).
   GMCC, 1987: Annual Report No. 16.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (B. Bodhaine, ed.).
   Gillette, D.A., W.D. Komhyr, L.S. Waterman, L.P. Steele, and R.H. Gammon, 1987: The NOAA/GMCC continuous CO<SUB>2</SUB> record at the South Pole,
      1975-1982. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 92, 4231-4240.
   GMCC, 1988: Annual Report No. 17.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (J. Elkins, ed.).
   GMCC, 1989: Annual Report No. 18.  NOAA, U.S. Department of Commerce (W. Komhyr, ed.).


</PRE>
