<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Trends of Syowa Station Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Syowa Station, Antarctica<BR>
</P></H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : February 1984 - January 1989
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Syowa Station          <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Antarctica               <B>Submmited by</B> : National Institute of Polar Research
<B>Latitude</B>  : 69&#176; 00&#180; S              <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 39&#176; 35&#180; E              <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : Observer's Standard Gas
<B>Altitude</B>  : 23 m                   <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="SyowaStation-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Shuji AOKI <SUP>1)</SUP>  and Takakiyo NAKAZAWA <SUP>2)</SUP>

               1) National Institute of Polar Research, Ministry of Education of Japan
                  1-9-10 Kaga, Itabashi, Tokyo 173, Japan

               2) Center for Atmospheric and Oceanic Studies, Faculty of Science, Tohoku University
                  Aoba, Sendai 980, Japan

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   69&#176; 00&#180; S 39&#176; 35&#180; E. East Ongul Island, Ltzow-Holm Bay, East Queen Maude Land, East Antarctica.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurements technique :</B>
   NDIR continuous.  Sampling with 8 m-high air intake, 30 m apart from the laboratory.
   Water vapour was removed from air samples by a glass trap cooled at -60&#176;C by an electric refrigerator.
   Standard gases were used for calibration every 30 minutes. Precision of the system was checked every 10 days.

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>

<B>Calibration gases used :</B> CO<SUB>2</SUB> in air.  

<B>Scale of reported data :</B> Gravimetric Scale 

<B>Literature references to programme :</B>
   Tanaka M., T. Nakazawa, M. Shiobara, H. Oshima, S. Aoki, S. Kawaguchi, T. Yamanouchi, Y. Makino and H. Murayama, 1987:
        Variations of tropospheric carbon dioxide concentration at Syowa Station (69&#176; 00&#180; S, 39&#176; 35&#180; E), Antarctica.
        <I>Tellus</I> 39B, 72-79.
   Nakazawa T., S. Aoki, S. Murayama, M. Fukabori, T. Yamanouchi, H. Murayama, M. Shiobara, G. Hashida, S. Kawaguchi and M. Tanaka, 1992:
        The concentration of atmospheric carbon dioxide at the Japanese Antarctic Station, Syowa. <I>Tellus</I>, 43B, 126-135.
   Aoki S., T. Nakazawa, S. Murayama, M. Fukabori, T. Yamanouchi, H. Murayama, M. Shiobara, S. Kawaguchi and M. Tanaka, 1992:
        Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide Measurements at Syowa Station, Antarctica, 1984-1988. <I>Proceedings NIPR Symposium of Polar Meteorology
        and Glaciology</I>, 5, 66-75.



</PRE>
<B>
<HR SIZE=5><HR SIZE=5 WIDTH=80%>
