<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Urawa Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/UrawaLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Urawa Station, Japan
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : April 1991 - March 1994
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Urawa               <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Japan                    <B>Submmited by</B> : Institute of Environmental Pollution of Saitama
<B>Latitude</B>  :  35&#176; 52&#180; N          <B>Time Interval</B>    : Continuous               <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 139&#176; 37&#180; E          <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 30 m                <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="Urawa-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
<B>Authors      :</B> Shigeru MACHIDA     

<B>Organization :</B> Institute of Environmental Pollution of Saitama, Japan

<B>Address      :</B> 639-1 Kami-okubo, Urawa City, Saitama 338, Japan

<B>Site Position and description :</B>
   35&#176; 51&#180; 55" N, 139&#176; 36&#180; 59" E, elevation 30 meter,
   Urban area, about 30 km north of Tokyo, center of Kanto plane which is one of mostly
   populated area in Japan.

<B>Sampling method, frequency and measurement technique :</B>
   Continuous NDIR analyzer,  HORIBA VIA-500R.
   Air from intake of 20 meter above ground is introduced to the dryers corresponding to +5, -30,
   and -65&#176;C dew-point temperature.
   The calibration is carried out 2-hourly using quadratic calibration equation with 4 working
   standards.
   Japan Standard Time of 9 hours earlier than UTC is adopted for the measurement.

<B>Scientific aims and scope of measurements :</B>
   Monitor atmospheric CO<SUB>2</SUB> variation.

<B>Data selection procedures used :</B>
   (1) Take the arithmetic mean of 30-second averaged value for one hour, and
   (2) adopt hourly mean value of which standard deviation less than 3ppmv.
   (3) Determine the best fit curve consisted of four harmonics and linears for the daily
       data of one year.
   (4) Reject the daily data exceeding 2 sigma ( sigma : standard deviation for daily data remained
       of one year) from the best fit curve, and
   (5) back to (4) until the difference of new and former sigma is less than 0.05ppmv.
   (6) The daily mean value with the difference from the final curve equal to or less than 5ppmv are
       selected as daily data.
   (7) Take the arithmetic mean of selected daily data as monthly data.

<B>Calibration gases used :</B>
   CO<SUB>2</SUB> in synthetic air (1991.4.1 - 1993.5.12)
   CO<SUB>2</SUB> in natural air   (1993.5.13 - )

<B>Scale of reported data :</B>
   WMO X1985 mole fraction scale, periodically calibrated at the headquarters of Japan Meteorological
   Agency, Tokyo.


</PRE>
<B>
