<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WDCGG - Trends of Christmas Island Monthly Mean CO2
</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/wdcgg/SiteLocation/ChristmasIslandLocation.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE>
Christmas Island, Kiribati
</H1></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Covering period : March 1984 - December 1993
</P>
<HR>

<PRE>
<B>Station</B>   : Christmas Islan        <B>Country/Trretory</B> : Kiribati                 <B>Submmited by</B> : NOAA/CMDL
<B>Latitude</B>  :  01&#176; 42&#180; N             <B>Time Interval</B>    : By Event                 <B>Analysis</B>     : NDIR
<B>Longitude</B> : 157&#176; 10&#180; W             <B>Unit</B>             : ppmv                     <B>Calibration</B>  : WMO X85 Scale
<B>Altitude</B>  : 3 m                    <B>Classification</B>   : Provisional              <B>Facility</B>     : Scripps Institution of Oceanography
</PRE>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLEBORDER="10">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="ChristmasIslandNoaa-CO2.gif">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<PRE>
        The following is an explanatory note, though a little modified, cited by the WDCGG from the
explanatory note of the NOAA Flask Network.

        NOAA/CMDL has attempted to provide the most accurate and precise measurements possible in a
timely manner.   NOAA/CMDL reserves the right to adjust the data based on recalibrations of reference
gases and instruments.   The CO<SUB>2</SUB> mixing ratios reported were measured by a nondispersive infrared
absorption technique in air samples collected in glass flasks at NOAA/CMDL flask network sites.  
Descriptions of the sampling, measurement, and calibration procedures are given in <I>Komhyr et al.</I>, 1983;
<I>Komhyr et al.</I>, 1985; and <I>Thoning et al.</I>, 1987.  Analysis and interpretation of the data have been
reported by <I>Komhyr et al.</I>, 1985; <I>Conway et al.</I>,1988; <I>Tans et al.</I>, 1989; <I>Tans et al.</I>, 1990 and <I>Conway
et al.</I>, 1994.  Thirty seven of the land-based sites were active in 1992.  Sampling at Ocean Station Charlie
was discontinued in 1973, and sampling at St. Croix was discontinued in 1990.   Also included are data
from three shipboard flask sampling programs.  Samples are collected at approximately 5 degree latitude
intervals on regular cruises of the Southland Star and Wellington Star in the Pacific Ocean between the
west coast of the U.S. and New Zealand.  Samples are also collected at 3 degree latitude intervals aboard
the Carla A. Hills on regular cruises in the South China Sea between Hong Kong and Singapore.   The
Data Report doesn't include the data of Carla A. Hills because they have not been updated since last
Report publishing.   The data contain CO<SUB>2</SUB> mixing ratios and relevant sampling and analysis information
for each flask sample. The monthly means were calculated from a smooth curve obtained by a combination of
curve fitting and digital filtering based on the methods of <I>Thoning et al.</I>, 1989, and <I>Tans et al.</I>, 1989b.
For Southland Star and Wellington Star, the sampling frequency in each latitude bin is insufficient to
calculate monthly means.   Therefore, NOAA/CMDL has merged the Southland Star's and Wellington Star's data
for each bin, and calculated monthly means for the fourteen 5-degree latitude bins from 30 degrees north
to 35 degrees south.

== REFERENCES ==
Conway, T.J., P.P. Tans, L.S. Waterman, K.W. Thoning, K.A. Masarie, and R.H. Gammon, 1988:
    Atmospheric carbon dioxide measurements in the remote global troposphere, 1981-1984. <I>Tellus</I>,
    40B, 81-115.
Conway, T.J., P.P Tans, L.S. Waterman, K.W. Thoning, D.R. Kitzis, K.A. Masarie, and N. Zhang,
    1994: Evidence for interannual variability of the carbon cycle from the National Oceanic and
    Atmospheric Administration/Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory global air sampling
    network. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 99, 22831-22855.
Komhyr, W.D., L.S. Waterman, and W.R. Taylor, 1983: Semiautomatic nondispersive infrared analyzer
    apparatus for CO<SUB>2</SUB> air sample analyses. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 88, 1315-1322.
Komhyr, W.D., R.H. Gammon, T.B. Harris, L.S. Waterman, T.J. Conway, W.R. Taylor, and K.W. Thoning,
    1985: Global atmospheric CO2 distribution and variations from 1968-1982 NOAA/GMCC CO<SUB>2</SUB> flask sample
    data. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, 90, 5567-5596.
